#. <section class="sutta" id="sn21.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn21.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 21"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 21"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhuvagga"
msgstr "1. Monks"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Theranāmakasutta → theranāmo (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn21.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Theranāmakasutta"
msgstr "10. A Mendicant Named Senior"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.283"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn21.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu theranāmako ekavihārī ceva hoti "
"ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time there was a certain mendicant named Senior. He lived alone "
"and praised living alone."

msgctxt "sn21.10:1.3"
msgid ""
"So eko gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisati eko paṭikkamati eko raho nisīdati eko caṅkamaṃ "
"adhiṭṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"He entered the village for alms alone, returned alone, sat in private alone, "
"and concentrated on walking meditation alone."

msgctxt "sn21.10:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te "
"bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn21.10:1.5"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, aññataro bhikkhu theranāmako ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca "
"vaṇṇavādī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, there’s a certain mendicant named Senior who lives alone and praises "
"living alone.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.10:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "So the Buddha said to a certain monk:"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena theraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehi:"
msgstr "“Please, monk, in my name tell the mendicant Senior that"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.3"
msgid "‘satthā taṃ, āvuso thera, āmantetī’”ti."
msgstr "the teacher summons him.”"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā thero "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ theraṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Venerable Senior and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.5"
msgid "“satthā taṃ, āvuso thera, āmantetī”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend Senior, the teacher summons you.”"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā thero tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ theraṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, reverend,” that monk replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat "
"down to one side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.7"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, thera, ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is it really true, Senior, that you live alone and praise living alone?”"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.9"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, thera, ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti?"
msgstr "“But in what way do you live alone and praise living alone?”"

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.10"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, eko gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisāmi eko paṭikkamāmi eko raho "
"nisīdāmi eko caṅkamaṃ adhiṭṭhāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Well, sir, I enter the village for alms alone, return alone, sit in private "
"alone, and concentrate on walking meditation alone."

msgctxt "sn21.10:2.11"
msgid "Evaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I live alone and praise living alone.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.10:3.1"
msgid "“Attheso, thera, ekavihāro neso natthīti vadāmi."
msgstr "“That is a kind of living alone, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "sn21.10:3.2"
msgid "Api ca, thera, yathā ekavihāro vitthārena paripuṇṇo hoti "
msgstr "But as to how living alone is fulfilled in detail, "

msgctxt "sn21.10:3.3"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn21.10:3.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho … pe …."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” he replied."

msgctxt "sn21.10:3.5"
msgid "“Kathañca, thera, ekavihāro vitthārena paripuṇṇo hoti."
msgstr "“And how, Senior, is living alone fulfilled in detail?"

# See BB’s note. I don’t get why he’s puzzled about the use of the plural form. Surely it just means “one’s own body and the bodies of others.”
msgctxt "sn21.10:3.6"
msgid ""
"Idha, thera, yaṃ atītaṃ taṃ pahīnaṃ, yaṃ anāgataṃ taṃ paṭinissaṭṭhaṃ, "
"paccuppannesu ca attabhāvapaṭilābhesu chandarāgo suppaṭivinīto."
msgstr ""
"It’s when what’s in the past is given up, what’s in the future is "
"relinquished, and desire and greed for present incarnations is eliminated."

msgctxt "sn21.10:3.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, thera, ekavihāro vitthārena paripuṇṇo hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how living alone is fulfilled in detail.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.284"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.10:4.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn21.10:4.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.10:5.1"
msgid "“Sabbābhibhuṃ sabbaviduṃ sumedhaṃ,"
msgstr "“The sage, champion, knower of all,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.10:5.2"
msgid "Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalittaṃ;"
msgstr "is unsullied in the midst of all things."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.10:5.3"
msgid "Sabbañjahaṃ taṇhākkhaye vimuttaṃ,"
msgstr "He’s given up all, freed in the ending of craving:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.10:5.4"
msgid "Tamahaṃ naraṃ ekavihārīti brūmī”ti."
msgstr "I declare that man to be one who lives alone.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn21.10:5.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
